# 🌴 Travel Agency Booking API — Spring Boot Back-End

A RESTful back-end service built with **Spring Boot** and **Spring Data JPA** for a travel agency vacation booking platform. This project modernizes a legacy back-end by migrating it to the Spring framework, exposing clean REST endpoints consumed by an Angular front-end.

> Built as part of **WGU D288 — Back-End Programming**

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Language | Java |
| Framework | Spring Boot |
| ORM | Spring Data JPA (Hibernate) |
| Database | MySQL |
| REST Layer | Spring Data REST |
| Build Tool | Maven |
| IDE | IntelliJ IDEA (Ultimate) |
| Utilities | Lombok |

---

## Features

- **Entity modeling** — Java entity classes mapped to a relational MySQL database following a UML class diagram, including an enum type
- **Repository layer** — JPA repository interfaces with cross-origin (CORS) support for each entity
- **Service layer** — Checkout service with purchase/order processing logic and order tracking number generation
- **REST Controller** — Checkout endpoint (`POST /api/checkout/purchase`) to place customer orders
- **Input Validation** — Bean Validation annotations enforcing data integrity required by the Angular front-end
- **Sample Data Seeding** — Five sample customers pre-loaded into the database on startup (idempotent)
- **Full-stack integration** — Tested end-to-end with an Angular front-end, supporting vacation bookings with multiple excursions per order

---

## Project Structure

```
src/main/java/com/example/travelagency/
├── config/
│   └── RestDataConfig.java
├── controllers/
│   └── CheckoutController.java
├── dao/
│   ├── CartItemRepository.java
│   ├── CartRepository.java
│   ├── CustomerRepository.java
│   ├── ExcursionRepository.java
│   └── VacationRepository.java
├── entities/
│   ├── Cart.java
│   ├── CartItem.java
│   ├── Customer.java
│   ├── Excursion.java
│   ├── Vacation.java
│   └── StatusType.java   ← enum
└── services/
    ├── CheckoutService.java          ← interface
    ├── CheckoutServiceImpl.java      ← implementation
    ├── Purchase.java                 ← request data class
    └── PurchaseResponse.java         ← response data class
```

---

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Java 17+
- MySQL 8.x
- Maven
- IntelliJ IDEA (Ultimate Edition recommended)

### Setup

1. **Clone the repository**
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/travel-agency-booking-api.git
   cd travel-agency-booking-api
   ```

2. **Configure the database**

   Update `src/main/resources/application.properties` with your MySQL credentials:
   ```properties
   spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/your_database
   spring.datasource.username=your_username
   spring.datasource.password=your_password
   spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=update
   ```

3. **Run the application**
   ```bash
   mvn spring-boot:run
   ```

   The API will start at `http://localhost:8080`.

---

## API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `POST` | `/api/checkout/purchase` | Place a vacation order with excursions |
| `GET` | `/api/vacations` | List all available vacation packages |
| `GET` | `/api/excursions` | List all available excursions |
| `GET` | `/api/customers` | List all customers |

> Additional REST endpoints are auto-generated by Spring Data REST for each repository.

---

## Sample Request

```json
POST /api/checkout/purchase
{
  "customer": {
    "firstName": "Jane",
    "lastName": "Doe",
    "email": "jane.doe@example.com",
    "address": "123 Main St"
  },
  "cart": {
    "vacation": { "id": 1 }
  },
  "cartItems": [
    { "excursion": { "id": 2 } },
    { "excursion": { "id": 5 } }
  ]
}
```

**Response:**
```json
{
  "orderTrackingNumber": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890"
}
```

